chart.description: Total CPU usage by containers in cluster(s)
chart.name: CPU
chart.programText: A = data('container_cpu_percent', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='rate').sum().publish(label='A')

chart.description: Network traffic into container's pod in bits/sec
chart.name: Network In
chart.programText: A = data('pod_network_receive_bytes_total', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('kubernetes_pod_name', '*') and filter('container_spec_name', '*'), rollup='rate').scale(8).publish(label='A')

chart.description: Total network traffic out of cluster in bits/sec
chart.name: Network Out
chart.programText: A = data('pod_network_transmit_bytes_total', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*'), rollup='rate').scale(8).sum().publish(label='A')

chart.description: Network traffic out of container's pod in bits/sec
chart.name: Network Out
chart.programText: A = data('pod_network_transmit_bytes_total', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('kubernetes_pod_name', '*') and filter('container_spec_name', '*'), rollup='rate').scale(8).publish(label='A')

chart.description: Top 10 CPU usage by containers in cluster(s)
chart.name: CPU
chart.programText: A = data('container_cpu_percent', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*', match_missing=True), rollup='rate').top(count=10).sum(by=['container_id', 'container_spec_name']).publish(label='A')

chart.name: CPU

publishLabelOptions.displayName: Cumulative cpu utilization as a percentage of the total host CPU available
publishLabelOptions.label: B

chart.programText: B = data('container_cpu_percent', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('kubernetes_pod_name', '*') and filter('container_name', '*'), rollup='rate').publish(label='B')

chart.description: Top 10 memory usage by containers in cluster(s)
chart.name: Memory Usage
chart.programText:
A = data('container_memory_usage_bytes', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*'), rollup='latest', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=2).top(count=10).publish(label='A')
B = data('container_spec_memory_limit_bytes', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*'), rollup='latest').sum().publish(label='B', enable=False)

chart.description: Total memory used by containers in cluster(s)
chart.name: Memory Usage
chart.programText: A = data('container_memory_usage_bytes', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*'), rollup='latest', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=2).sum().publish(label='A')

chart.description: Container memory usage in bytes. Additionally the container memory limit will be plotted if the container memory limit was configured.
chart.name: Memory Usage
chart.programText:
A = data('container_memory_usage_bytes', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('kubernetes_pod_name', '*') and filter('container_spec_name', '*'), rollup='latest', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=2).publish(label='A')
B = data('container_spec_memory_limit_bytes', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('kubernetes_pod_name', '*') and filter('container_spec_name', '*'), rollup='latest').publish(label='B')

chart.description: Number of disk writes per second by container
chart.name: Disk Writes

publishLabelOptions.displayName: Cumulative count of seconds spent writing
publishLabelOptions.label: B

chart.programText:
A = data('container_fs_writes_total', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('kubernetes_pod_name', '*') and filter('container_spec_name', '*'), rollup='latest', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=2).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = data('container_fs_write_seconds_total', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*') and filter('kubernetes_node', '*') and filter('kubernetes_pod_name', '*') and filter('container_spec_name', '*'), rollup='latest', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=2).publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = (A/B).publish(label='C')

chart.description: This may include "pause" containers used internally by K8s
chart.name: # Active Containers
chart.programText: A = data('container_cpu_utilization', filter=filter('kubernetes_cluster', '*') and filter('kubernetes_namespace', '*') and filter('sf_tags', '*'), rollup='latest').count().publish(label='A')
